All Classes

Class Description
AbstractAnalysisResult
This abstract class represents a generic result of an analysis of a single commit.
AbstractCommitAnalyzer
This abstract class defines the methods to be implemented by and the common elements, like the global Logger, for each specific commit analyzer.
AbstractCommitExtractor
This abstract class defines the methods to be implemented by and the common elements, like the global Logger, for each specific commit extractor.
AbstractManager
This abstract class defines common methods and elements of the specific commit extraction and analysis managers.
AnalysisManager
This class manages the entire commit analysis process.
AnalysisSetupException
Custom exception indicating and describing problems while setting-up an analysis.
ChangedArtifact
This class represents a changed artifact as provided by the diff of a commit.
ComAnI
The main class of this tool for preparing and starting the internal processes.
Commit
This class represents a commit of a version control system.
CommitQueue
This class realizes a commit queue.
CommitQueue.QueueState
This enumeration defines the different states of the commit queue.
CommitSerializer
This class provides capabilities to save individual Commit objects as CDMS-files and to read such files for creating Commit objects based on their CDMS-elements.
ExtractionManager
This class manages the entire commit extraction process.
ExtractionSetupException
Custom exception indicating and describing problems while setting-up an extractor.
FileUtilities
This class provides utility methods for creating, deleting, and checking files and directories.
IAnalysisQueue
This interface declares the methods a CommitQueue has to implement for its use by a commit analysis.
IExtractionQueue
This interface declares the methods a CommitQueue has to implement for its use by a commit extractor.
InfrastructureUtilities
This class provides utility methods for the main infrastructure, like updating the classpath.
Logger
This class is used to print different types of information to the console.
Logger.LogLevel
This enumeration defines the different log levels.
Logger.MessageType
This enumeration defines the different types of messages.
ProcessUtilities
This class provides utility methods for executing commands as external Process and returning corresponding ProcessUtilities.ExecutionResults.
Setup
This class reads the configuration file and provides the user-defined properties for other components of the tool.
SetupException
This class represents the specific type of exception thrown if checking and preparing the properties fails at some point, e.g., due to missing information, false arguments, etc.
VerificationRelevantResult
This class represents a specific commit analysis result, which provides information about code, build, and variability model artifacts affected by the changes of the analyzed commit.
